  <h2>Standards and Expectations</h2>
  <p>
    Property management standards for office towers typically reference ISO quality management, WHS compliance, public liability and professional indemnity insurance at appropriate levels, and building-specific access protocols that must be formally agreed before cleaning commences.
  </p>
  <p>
    Green Star building certifications may impose specific environmental cleaning requirements including eco-product registers and waste management reporting. A-grade buildings typically require documented KPIs, digital reporting and regular performance review meetings. aligning commercial tower procurement with government procurement standards.
  </p>

