  <h2>How CPC Delivers Office Tower Cleaning</h2>
  <p>
    CPC manages office tower cleaning through dedicated site teams with consistent after-hours supervision, digital inspection tools that capture real-time performance data and photographic evidence, and centralised contract management providing building managers with portfolio-level visibility. Building management reporting is formatted to align with property manager and strata management requirements.
  </p>
  <p>
    Access management, key control and security system integration are managed through CPC's documented procedures, reviewed and approved by building management at contract commencement and updated whenever building access arrangements change.
  </p>

  <h2>Workforce and Training Model</h2>
  <p>
    CPC operates a vetted workforce model combining directly employed core staff with contractor partners who meet our compliance, training and screening requirements. Office tower workforce are trained in after-hours access protocols, building security procedures, chemical management in occupied environments, and escalation requirements for after-hours incidents.
  </p>
  <p>
    Supervisors conduct nightly floor inspections and are contactable throughout the cleaning window. Consistent workforce deployment minimises retraining burden and supports building security requirements around known personnel in the building after hours.
  </p>

  <h2>Reporting, Auditing and Evidence of Work</h2>
  <p>CPC provides building managers with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Digital inspection reports for all completed shifts, including photographic evidence</li>
    <li>Defect management records with timestamped resolution evidence</li>
    <li>Attendance logs confirming service delivery on the required nights</li>
    <li>Portfolio-level reporting for multi-building property management groups</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Reporting frequency and format is aligned to building management requirements and can be integrated into existing property management reporting workflows without requiring additional manual processing.
